The global heat-resistant coating market is segmented based on resin type, technology, end-use industry, and region. In terms of resin type, the market is categorized into silicone, epoxy, acrylic, polyester, and others. Silicone-based heat-resistant coatings are widely used due to their excellent thermal stability. By technology, the market is divided into water-based, solvent-based, and powder-based coatings. Water-based coatings are gaining popularity due to their low VOC emissions and environmental sustainability. The end-use industries for heat-resistant coatings include automotive, aerospace, construction, marine, and others. The automotive sector is a significant consumer of heat-resistant coatings for engine components and exhaust systems. Geographically, the market is analyzed across North America, Europe, Asia-Pacific, South America, and the Middle East & Africa.

